 important for their work. We also found that the majority of open\nsource contributors at UC are project maintainers, meaning they are the primary\nstewards of a project. Despite the importance and prevalence of open source\nsoftware, about one-third of respondents reported that they have shared their\ncode on custom websites, indicating that a large body of academic software is\nnot located in standard repositories. Contributors face many challenges in terms\nof resources, computing infrastructure, and institutional culture. At the same\ntime, the abundance of maintainers and the prevalence of time and\nfunding-related challenges underscore a critical need for support for\nmaintenance costs and overall sustainability of open source software.","position":{"start":{"line":69,"column":1},"end":{"line":69,"column":1}},"key":"WDmfra8eq7"}],"key":"JuRKRq0cjk"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":81,"column":1},"end":{"line":81,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Advice for Open Source Program Offices (OSPOs)","position":{"start":{"line":81,"column":1},"end":{"line":81,"column":1}},"key":"Aor7iTMhN1"}],"identifier":"advice-for-open-source-program-offices-ospos","label":"Advice for Open Source Program Offices (OSPOs)","html_id":"advice-for-open-source-program-offices-ospos","implicit":true,"key":"NjJBIElFZI"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":83,"column":1},"end":{"line":97,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":83,"column":1},"end":{"line":88,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":83,"column":1},"end":{"line":87,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The most common challenges that emerged from our study were ","position":{"start":{"line":83,"column":1},"end":{"line":83,"column":1}},"key":"q8L4fNhDIE"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":83,"column":1},"end":{"line":83,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"time and\nfunding","position":{"start":{"line":83,"column":1},"end":{"line":83,"column":1}},"key":"t9Ha2qSgXg"}],"key":"s4cpNkAu6l"},{"type":"text","value":". As such, OSPOs should consider either directly funding open source,\nor consider creative ways to “give back” time or money. Examples might include\nfacilitating co-working groups, promoting AI tools for documentation, or\nproviding support for external grant acquisition.","position":{"start":{"line":83,"column":1},"end":{"line":83,"column":1}},"key":"HtC20Vk5o5"}],"key":"nZljmvWvD4"}],"key":"qVlGxDYI7x"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":92,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":91,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We encountered high demand for affordable, accessible, feature-rich computing\nenvironments. This suggests an opportunity for academic OSPOs to help secure\nthe ","position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":89,"column":1}},"key":"ZUQOz7eggy"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":89,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"technical infrastructure","position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":89,"column":1}},"key":"g0mx71ImvL"}],"key":"ezNVziLPnZ"},{"type":"text","value":" needed for open source development.","position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":89,"column":1}},"key":"PwC6KudGep"}],"key":"qEbMTzQn3E"}],"key":"qxZdR1LaW4"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":93,"column":1},"end":{"line":97,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":93,"column":1},"end":{"line":96,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Comments revealed three broad categories of concern: ","position":{"start":{"line":93,"column":1},"end":{"line":93,"column":1}},"key":"nwRjYXkag4"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":93,"colum